de.oaam.model.oaam.capabilities

Interface ResourceConsumption

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, OaamBaseElementA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ResourceConsumptionImpl

    public interface ResourceConsumption
extends OaamBaseElementA
    A representation of the model object 'Resource Consumption'. A resource consumption is the definition of how many resource of a single type are required for a capability. In addition, the original resource type can be referenced.

    The following features are supported:

    • Count
    • Original Resource
    • Type
    See Also:
    CapabilitiesPackage.getResourceConsumption()

      • getOriginalResource

        org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<Resource> getOriginalResource()
        Returns the value of the 'Original Resource' reference list. The list contents are of type Resource. References the original resources of that were required by the type. These might differ from the capabilities resource due to resource alternatives. Capability resource are those realy consumed. Original resources are those originally demanded.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Original Resource' reference list.
        See Also:
        CapabilitiesPackage.getResourceConsumption_OriginalResource()
